:"Peter","meanings":["form of the name of the best-known of all Christ's apostles, traditionally regarded as the founder of the Christian Church. The name derives, via Latin, from Greek <i>petros</i> ‘stone, rock’. This is used as a translation of the Aramaic byname <i>Cephas</i>, given to the apostle  Simon  son of Jona, to distinguish him from another of the same name (  Simon Zelotes ). ‘When Jesus beheld him, he said, Thou art Simon the son of Jona: thou shalt be called Cephas, which is by interpretation, A stone’ (John 1:42). According to Matthew 16:17–18, Christ says more explicitly, ‘Blessed art thou, Simon Bar-jona … thou art Peter, and upon this rock I will build my church’. The name has been in continuous use since the Middle Ages."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1354684,"age":40,"year":"1200","julianDay":2159351,"description":"The Christian territory controlled the Kingdoms of Aragon, Navarre, and Castile.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"Segundo Pedro Ermíldez Portugalés was born about 1160, in Toledo, Castilla-La Mancha, Spain as the son of Ermildo Meléndez and Dama En Blanco. He married Blanca Pantoja in 1182, in Spain. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in 1217, at the age of 58, and was buried in Toledo, Castilla-La Mancha, Spain."},"et":{"about 1160–1217":"umbes 1160–1217","1129–Male":"1129–Surnud","1160–1217":"1160–1217","–1260":"–1260","–1261":"–1261","1162–Female":"1162–Surnud","1202–1280":"1202–1280","1100–1159":"1100–1159","–1160":"–1160","about 1160":"umbes 1160","1162":"1162","1261":"1261","1260":"1260","1160":"1160","1182":"1182","1280":"1280","1217":"1217","1129":"1129","1159":"1159","1202":"1202","1200":"1200","1100":"1100","about 1202":"umbes 1202","Toledo, Castilla-La Mancha, Spain":"Toledo, Castilla-La Mancha, Hispaania","Monasterio de Fuencaliente, Toledo, Castilla-La Mancha, España":"Toledo, Castilla-La Mancha, Hispaania","Spain":"Hispaania","of, Portugal":"Portugal"},"fi":{"about 1160–1217":"noin 1160–1217","1129–M